description:
About the project:

Our client is a powerful financial technology company that provides expense management solutions for businesses. With a strong focus on security and customer support, during the last 10 years, it has become a trusted partner for businesses of all sizes. The platform simplifies expense tracking, manages employee spending, and provides real-time financial insights. With their prepaid debit cards, businesses can set customized spending limits and restrictions to control company spending. Their robust reporting and analytics features allow businesses to make data-driven decisions and optimize their operations. Join us and revolutionize the way businesses manage their expenses with our client's innovative solutions.

Requirements:
• 3+ years of experience with .NET;
• Strong experience with .NET 6, Asp.NET, WebApi 2;
• Hands-on experience with .NET App Services and Azure Functions for developing scalable cloud-based solutions;
• Expertise in working with various data... storage systems, including MSSQL, MongoDB, Redis, and Azure Table Storage;
• Familiarity with message queues and communication patterns, such as RabbitMQ, Azure Service Bus, and Azure Storage Queues;
• Proficiency in front-end technologies, including HTML, CSS, and JavaScript;
• Knowledge of JavaScript Frameworks;
• At least Upper-Intermediate level of English.

Will be a plus:
• In-depth understanding of microservices architecture and the ability to design, develop, and deploy microservices-based applications;
• Financial experience(pref. credit, plaid integration).

Responsibilities:
• Self-led problem-solving skills and issue prioritization;
• Develop APIs, components, services, and technologies using modern technologies;
• Optimize critical areas of the application across all layers;
• Contribute to the design and implementation of system-level architecture.

